  "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nIn chat, the only way to dismiss the input is to tap inside the chat history. Which often is made difficult when your chat history is covered by stickers and tapping inside invokes the sticker details modal. \r\nAll of the other messaging apps I tested allow you to drag the input toolbar down to dismiss it. Try WhatsApp, Signal, Messenger, iMessage, Discord, the list goes on. It's natural and what people came to expect in chat. Currently in Status, if I drag inside the input toolbar it will just scroll the chat. \r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n![ScreenFlow](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/73437969-93d56500-434d-11ea-9b30-ea947e1a2918.gif)\r\n\r\nIf user starts dragging his finger from or across the input toolbar, the toolbar begins to follow his gesture. It has a tolerance, so dragging it more than halfway down should dismiss it, dragging it less than half should return to focused position. The toolbar and keyboard always follow the gesture of your finger, both up and down.\r\n\r\n![ScreenFlow2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/73439160-7d300d80-434f-11ea-83c2-8381314e3d23.gif) \r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nOur input toolbar behaves exactly like every other messaging app out there following user's gesture to drag it vertically.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nüôè  Thanks!! üôè \r\n",
